-- Fujitsu looking to buy IBM's server business - WSJ
-- By Neha Alawadhi in Bangalore
-- Wed Jan 22, 2014 12:04PM EST
-- None



Jan 22 (Reuters) - Japan's Fujitsu Ltd <6702.T> is considering buying International Business Machines Corp's <IBM.N> low-end server business, the Wall Street Journal reported on Wednesday, citing people familiar with the matter.

Fujitsu and IBM could not be reached for comment. Recent reports have identified Lenovo Group Ltd <0992.HK> and Dell Inc as potential buyers of the x86 server unit, which powers corporate data centers. [ID:nL2N0KU0SC]